# Plan 28.4 Stage 2 acceptance: prove `rule_implementation_wrapper` is
# in the analysis call path. The fixture's defs.bzl defines a Starlark
# rule whose impl writes a sentinel string. With the wrapper wired, the
# wrapper IS invoked but is currently a no-op (`return implementation(raw_ctx)`),
# so the sentinel reaches the output unchanged. Test verifies output
# matches; if the wrapper were silently bypassed, we'd get the same
# result — so the meaningful follow-up here is the kuro-internal
# probe that intercepts wrapper invocations (filed as a Phase 28.4
# Stage 3 follow-up). For Stage 2 the acceptance is "no-op produces
# byte-for-byte equivalent providers", proven by this build target +
# the unchanged llvm:Demangle build.
